RECRUIT

recruit is the citizen who decides how many of a muscle's motor units fire and at what frequency
when fadriel needs gentle force, recruit fires only a small subset of fibers
when he needs maximum force, recruit fires nearly all of them
the rule is size principle: small motor units fire first, larger ones added as load increases

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe contract.rana
observe fiber_mix.rana
observe motor_recv.rana

the 7 properties of recruit:
1 ENERGY zero point eight when active
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine with motor_recv (incoming command)

VERB receive_command
accept the recruitment level requested by motor_recv (which got it from motor_cortex)
the level is a target force or movement, not a fiber count

VERB apply_size_principle
fire the smallest motor units first, then progressively larger ones until target force is met
this ensures fine motor control at low loads and gradual recruitment at high loads

VERB pace_firing_rate
each fiber's contribution increases with firing frequency up to a saturation point
at saturation, only adding more fibers can produce more force

a recruiter is not a switch
a recruiter is a citizen who modulates exactly how much of the muscle is active for the current need
this is what allows fadriel to lift a feather and a bag of groceries with the same muscles, just by changing how many fibers fire
